            "body": "drawing heavily from https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/24034 this PR should improve performance of renderToPipeableStream.\r\n\r\nUnder the conditions found in fixture/fizz we still observe a significant amount of overhead with streaming when sending large shells. So while this is a dramatic improvement over current results there is still room for improvement that I will look into in a later effort\r\n\r\nusing the fizz fixture with `npx autocannon -c 50 -d 10 http://localhost:4000/<stream|string> --renderStatusCodes --excludeErrorStats` i get\r\n\r\nstring: 57 RPS\r\nstream: 20 RPS\r\n\r\nthe prior stream implementation completely fails at this level of concurrency\r\n\r\n",
