            "author_association": "NONE",
            "active_lock_reason": null,
            "body": "When using React type definitions and hooks, have the option to highlight preferred way of using them.\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nimport React, {useState} from 'react';\r\n\r\nconst Example = () => {\r\n    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);\r\n    ...\r\n    return <>count</>;\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\ntechnically you could do this as well:\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nimport React from 'react';\r\n\r\nconst Example: React.FunctionComponent = () => {\r\n    const [count, setCount] = React.useState(0);\r\n    ...\r\n    return <>count</>;\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is a basic example but if you use a lot of hooks and what not, you can understand how it can get ugly.\r\nFor consistency I'd like to suggest an added rule to [eslint-plugin-react-hooks](https://www.npmjs.com/package/eslint-plugin-react-hooks) to prefer definitions/hooks to not be used with the `React` namespace.\r\n\r\nI know the [Introducing Hooks](https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-intro.html) documentation shows it like the first example and I prefer it that way as well.  I assume that is the React preferred way.",
